P(\text{all three are hearts}) = \left(\cfrac{13}{52}\right)^3 = \cfrac{1}{64}
P(\text{not all three are hearts}) = 1-P(\text{all three are hearts}) = \cfrac{63}{64}
P(\text{none of three is heart}) = \left(\cfrac{39}{52}\right)^3 = \cfrac{27}{64}
